SIMPLE: marijuana
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: marijuana
<hw>marijuana</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A strong-smelling
Asian plant (<spn>Cannabis sativa</spn>), also called
<altname>hemp</altname>, from which a number of euphorogenic and
hallucinogenic drugs are prepared. The euphoric effect is predominantly
due to <prod>tetrahydrocannabinol</prod> (<prod>THC</prod>).</def>
<altsp>[Also spelled <asp>marihuana</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> cannabis, ganja, pot, grass, marihuana,
<spn>Cannabis sativa</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The dried leaves or the female flowers of the hemp
plant, which is smoked or chewed to obtain a euphoric effect. The
flowers usually have a higher concentration of the active ingredient,
tetrahydrocannabinol.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> cannabis, ganja, pot, grass, marihuana, dope, weed,
gage, sess, sens, smoke, skunk, Mary Jane.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Marikina</ent>⟦br⟧
